SIMPLE: captivity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Captivity
<hw>Cap*tiv"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>captivitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>captivit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being a captive or a prisoner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>More celebrated in his <qex>captivity</qex> that in his greatest
triumphs.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A state of being under control; subjection of the
will or affections; bondage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sink in the soft <qex>captivity</qex> together.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Imprisonment; confinement; bondage; subjection;
servitude; slavery; thralldom; serfdom.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Captor</ent>⟦br⟧
